Detailed Description: Through dialogue, we come into contact with the paranormal. You are a counselor at a facility for children with hidden paranormal abilities. You must fill in the chart with dialogue and observation within the limited time of 60 minutes. Children with various different paranormal abilities The most important thing you need to find out is the details of their hidden paranormal abilities. We need to know what abilities they have, what triggers them to manifest, and how to deal with them. However, the children you counsel are unique and challenging to work with. Observe them and communicate with them to see which approaches work the best. Point-and-click conversation The game is a point-and-click format. You can communicate with them by using what is in the room or what they are wearing as conversation starters and by making choices that come up in the conversation. The more trust you gain from them, the more in-depth information you may learn. Conversely, if they are ever alarmed by you, your sanity will be at risk. Your understanding will change the outcome The more information you acquire and the more you fill out your medical records, the higher your reputation as a counselor will be. Aim to be a better counselor. Let's hope you don't run away during the process...

Detailed Description: It’s tough fighting evil by moonlight and being a normal 90s kid by daylight! Can you save your city’s dreams from invading monsters, halt a magical plague in its tracks, and still help your new club prepare for the school festival in time? Star Crystal Warriors Go! is an interactive novel by Holly McMasters. It's entirely text-based, without graphics or sound effects, and fueled by the vast, unstoppable power of your imagination. Ever since that talking animal showed up and gave you magical powers, you’ve become a Stellaria, a magical teenage warrior who can protect people’s dreams from the terrifying monsters you call Nightmares. Lately, your own dreams have been filled with visions of a crystal castle and a love that feels like a memory. How will you handle the Nightmares that threaten your city? Will you heal them with compassion or punish them with your magic? And who’s this true love you’re dreaming about? Is it your best friend who knows nothing about your magical adventures? The mysterious vigilante who shows up to every battle with a rose and a piece of pithy advice? Or the beautiful Nightmare with the enigmatic smile? As you learn the truth behind the Stellaria and the Nightmares, you’ll also learn the truth behind yourself. Will you keep your heart’s Star Crystal full of hope and defeat the Nightmares, or will you fall to despair and join the darkness? Play as male, female, or non-binary; gay, straight, bi, asexual, or poly. Magically manipulate dreams to fight monsters. Build a legacy with your new school club. Solve the mystery of a magical kingdom. Cure a magical sleeping plague. Find love at the school festival’s dance. Is your magic strong enough to save reality?

Detailed Description: The Work of Your Hands is a small-scale, deep, and relaxing open-world survival crafting game. You have no crafting screen or list of items. Harvest raw materials, create tools from them, build practical structures, and grow delicious food. You are in control of every step to live off the land. Inspired by the popular Minecraft mod Terrafirmacraft . Create Items Intuitively No more buying items from your crafting table or workbench when you have the right items - in The Work of Your Hands , you are fully in control of the item creation process. Pick up any raw materials and see how they can fit together to form a useful tool or larger component. Build Practical Structures Shelters you can create are inspired by real-world survival structures such as the debris hut. Grow Unique Food Gather, plant, nurture, and harvest the various unique plants found in this familiar but fantastic environment. Explore the World The world is not randomly generated. Every resource, plant, rock, and point of interest has been placed by hand for your discovery. Key Features For fans of survival games who want an immersive, relaxing, and deep experience Engaging and unique crafting system Created by a solo developer

Detailed Description: Unsure is an immersive, first-person, asymmetric horror game where players take on the role of cult survivor or demon. Four to six survivors, trapped in an abandoned asylum by a satanic cult, have been offered as sacrifices, and the demon must be sated. Once the cultists have summoned their demon, one of the game’s many possible killers, the hunt begins. To escape, survivors must evade the demon while searching the labyrinthine asylum for one of the hidden keys that will unlock an exit. For each survivor, there is one key and one exit. Upon finding a key, survivors must determine which one of the doors the key unlocks. When a survivor escapes, that exit is permanently locked behind them. The trick? One of the hidden keys is faulty, meaning that in each game, at least one door will not open, and at least one survivor will be sacrificed.

Detailed Description: Canterz Paranormies 2 is a 2D Top Down survival horror game based on the story of the most renowned paranormal investigation team of the US called Canterz Paranormies who got a request to investigate the house located in Kentucky, which is haunted by the spirits of the cemetery located a few miles away from the property. The Paranormal investigation team got a call from Jun, the owner of the Kentucky house, with a request to investigate her property. She said that an Evil spirit followed her home from the cemetery which she visited a few weeks ago for attending a funeral of one of her close relatives who passed away recently. A day after she returned home from the graveyard the paranormal activities started to pick up. Every day, she experienced the various paranormal activities like seeing dark apparitions, furniture moving on their own, unexplained banging noises, disembodied growling and laughing sounds, and foul smell coming from the basement area. She was feeling uneasy living in her own home and desperately needed help in order to get rid of this entity from her house. On top of that, she was really concerned for the safety of her family and her kids. So, she asked the 'Canterz Paranormies' team to investigate her home for the paranormal evidence and assist her to get rid of the dark entity for good. You play as James, the lead paranormal investigator of the 'Canterz Paranormies' team and your mission is to help her out at all costs! Are you ready to accept the challenge? Key Features: Explore the entire Kentucky haunted house! Use the various kinds of scientific equipment like Rem pod, SLS, Night vision cameras etc. Lots of Evil spirits lurking in the shadows. Explore the Spirit world, cemetery and basement area! Nearly half an hour of paranormal investigation! Note: I am a solo indie game developer and I have done all of the graphics, artwork, animation, character design, and programming except for the music. I hope you will enjoy the game.

Detailed Description: In the midst of the 2020 pandemic, when performing arts spaces were forced shut, a team of creative and tech collaborators began a mammoth task to document Centre 42's beloved blue house as its own virtual world. Through the process of photogrammetry, we captured a digital rendering of the building. The desire stemmed from preserving memories, but it led to the curiosity in exploring and expanding opportunities to create theatre and build community beyond physical spaces. The Cloud House journey brings the player to a futuristic rendering of Centre 42. It is an invitation to explore its new imagining within a virtual world. You will encounter our very first experience titled 'Love Letters to 42', a single-player filmic story shot in 2020 that captures the history of pre-pandemic C42 at 42 Waterloo Street. In Cloud House, audiences can encounter arts performances, experiences, workshops and interact with artists and other audiences. It is also an invitation and opportunity for digital artists, theatre-makers to imagine their works to be presented in this space. The content, programmes, interactivity functions are being imagined and built as ‘modules’ and updates along the way after this initial launch. The digital possibilities are endless! Please note: the game environment features bright neon lights and special effects, discretion is advised.

Detailed Description: The Forest is in Danger. Evil forces are absorbing what magic remains and destroying all in their path. Gain ancient knowledge from powerful spell books long forgotten and create alliances with magical creatures and Gods. Build your strength and defeat the invading forces. As a Keeper it is your sworn promise to protect the forest and maintaining the balance. Build your strength and defeat the invading forces. Use coins to build your deck Combine coins to gain more valuable coins Use your coins to acquire powerful spells and allies. Gain ancient knowledge from powerful spell books long forgotten. Acquiring spell books will give you knowledge of ancient magic. Combine magic spells to increase your mastery of the ancient, giving you more powerful spells. The power of Destruction and Healing await the chosen one. Create alliances with magical creatures and Gods. Many mysterious and mystical creatures reside in the forest. Gain their favor for additional strategic advantage. With enough favor you can sway the Gods to dominate your enemy. Keepers of the Forest is an epic, 2 player deck building game. Can be played alone against the computer or two local players can battle it out. Choose your hero to begin. Each of the 4 choices offers a different special ability (listed on each card) such as never having to discard or piercing through your opponent's protection with every damage dealt. Each player starts with the same 10 starter cards. Use the coins you draw into your hand to acquire new cards from the Keepers Row. Each card may give you health, damage, protection, more coins, or a combination of these. There are also many Keepers you can acquire that will allow you to do special things (written on each card). Some special rules include refreshing the keepers row - discarding up to all 5 of the drawn keepers and drawing new ones from the deck into the keepers row, combining cards in your discard pile, or immediately gaining spells into your discard pile. Cards may also require you to discard, or may allow you to draw an extra card, or even make your opponent discard a card (these are denoted as icons on the bottom of each card). The first player to bring their opponent to their knees, down to 0 health, wins!
Short Description: Keepers of the Forest is a 2 player deck building game that can be played alone against the computer or by two local players. Starting with the same 10 cards, buy from one deck to build your own deck try to deal enough damage to defeat your opponent. 1st to bring their opponent to 0 health wins!

Detailed Description: Test your skills and courage in Yōkaimaki, a 2D horror fishing and cooking simulation game from USC’s Open Alpha! In 19th century Japan, you’re a humble fisherman who has finally taken over your family’s sushi business. Cooking by day and fishing by night, you strive to uphold your family’s legacy. But once a year, during the blood moon, the fish that swim the sea give way to fearsome cryptids from the deep—the yōkai. Over the course of four nights, use your cursor to explore the ocean depths and hook the most fabled of monsters. Then, drag and drop in quick succession as you transform these strange creatures into the most delectable sushi in the land. And make sure to read your journal entries to discover the lore of the fascinatingly frightening world around you! The fate of the restaurant is in your hands! Can you keep your creatures and your customers reeling in?

Detailed Description: My Darkest Witch is a survival arena game where you take on the role of a mage from the Order of Light, battling waves of infected creatures. Alone, you stand against the abyss of darkness, striving to cleanse the world from the heretical plague. Strengthen your abilities, upgrade your weapons, and enhance your character to withstand increasingly powerful enemies. Each wave becomes more dangerous, testing your survival skills to the limit. Key features: Endless Waves of Enemies: Face progressively challenging waves of enemies that test your skills and adaptability. Each wave introduces new threats, forcing you to refine your strategy and stay on your toes as you battle against increasingly powerful monsters. Comprehensive Character and Ability Upgrades: Develop your character through a robust progression system that allows you to enhance your magical abilities and defensive skills. Choose your upgrades wisely to build a powerful mage capable of overcoming the toughest foes. Weapon Variety and Customization: Equip your mage with an array of mystical weapons, each with its own strengths and playstyle. Upgrade and customize your arsenal to suit your combat preferences, giving you the edge in battle against the ever-growing hordes. Atmospheric Arenas with Dynamic Combat: Immerse yourself in dark, foreboding arenas where the environment plays a key role in survival. Master the layout, adapt to the changing conditions, and use the surroundings to your advantage as you fight relentless enemies. Strategic Depth and Tactical Gameplay: My Darkest Witch offers more than just fast-paced action. The game encourages strategic planning, from choosing the right upgrades to positioning yourself for maximum effectiveness. Every decision matters as you fight to survive the endless onslaught.

Detailed Description: Gameplay This game is a puzzle-based VR space themed game. Player need to complete several puzzles in order to progress throughout the game. Several cutscenes are available between scenes. Player need to complete the puzzles accordingly since all the puzzles are gated among each other. In-game voice line will guide player to progress. In-game tutorial is also available for player to practice moving in a Zero-gravity environment using VR. Description Fallen Stars is a immersive First Person VR game that tells the story of a team of astronaut crew performing several duties on the space station. The story started by the user, Thomas Jackson, an astronaut from the present, searching the net for an article about the astronauts during a space mission in January 1975. But some white light flashed through and Thomas fainted. He woke up to be an astronaut from the past, Thomas William at the I.C.E.S 1 (International Centre Energy Space Station). Upon entering the station, Thomas William performed several duties including adjusting the radio frequency, fixing the power supplies and restore the wire connections. After that, three cosmonauts return to their spacecraft and re-enter earth. During their return to earth, unexpected things happen to them. This game challenges player to finish all the puzzles as soon as possible. Features Zero Gravity Movement which provide a very unique way to move in VR Immersive Space Station Environment in VR Easy to understand puzzles for player to play Tutorial option for those who want to experience Zero Gravity Movement before entering the main game Storytelling Cutscenes Voice acting between characters Immersive In-Game Music Fallen Stars is a game developed by FlyStar. We are a team of university students participating a program called DICE which challenges teams to develop a full-functioning VR Application in 3 months period. We do not have any background in game development and due to time constraints, several bugs are expected and the game is not fully optimized. However, we do appreciate all the supports! :)

Detailed Description: The Outsider TD is a top down view tower defense game with tons of action, explosions and silly humor. In this new take on the classic tower defense style game, you take on the role of Danny : A down on his luck fella who gets involved in a local gang when a much needed promise of fast cash arises. The towers are your crew members, each of which will have a unique weapons and upgrade options. Place your crew members strategically around the paths in front of your stash houses to maximize their efficiency against the waves of enemies that seek to thwart you. There are 4 main fractions to defend your warehouse against and ultimately defeat: 1) THE THUGSZ A smaller local gang that more than makes up for its size in relentlessness However, without a warehouse to manufactor product, they eagerly resort to taking it from whomever has a stash lying about. Molly gets her name from her favorite cocktail: The Molotov Cocktail 2) THE STEFAN CARTEL A well financed, even better dressed, covert outfit that blends in with everyday business men and women. They control a large piece of the drug market with futuristic weaponry which is maintained by the crew and in no way thanks to Stefan himself, who inherited the cartel from his father before naming it after himself shortly after Stefan would describe himself as a highly sophisticated, highly admired, highly dangerous individual who can neutralize a man from 1000 miles away, but nothing comes even close to his skills as a lover 3) THE BUTCHER the Butcher: a massive and scary fellow who deals in meat and chemicals (the iillegal kind) his gang is comprised of ruthless, violent, chemistry-huffing, lunatic lab workers. When they’re not creating deadly new drugs they’re attacking other cartels using unconventional methods. Whatever you do, do NOT mention his freakishly small head... 4) THE DEA With endless backing and endless funding the Drug Enforcement Army has a lot of options for Chief Boyd to choose from when hunting down pesky criminal organisations, making him and his army a tough customer for any criminal organisation to deal with, especially those who have an aversion to most armored vehicles and rocketry on their private property As you prove your stash house protection capabilities against rival gangs and the DEA, you advance in rank. Higher rank means more responsibility and bigger stash houses with more to protect and more cash on hand. But with more to loose comes more unwanted attention! Upgrade your towers, turrets and use your drone to defeat your rivals and take over! Ad the game to your wish list today and stay tuned for more exciting info, pics and videos about The Outsider TD

Top View 2D Shooter (SH m`Up Genre) SHMUP Inspired by the classic 90s shooter Thunder Force from Technosoft(テクノソフト) and the cop shooter M.U.S.H.A.(Alester) from (コンパイル) Based on retro game play, we pursued intuitive fun. Daggers tracking enemies, instantaneous Detshu functions, various subarms, energy shields, bodies of mercenaries and disciples of the same clan who assist Player, aircraft carrier-sized armed merchant ships, insect monsters bigger than imagination, and Battle Titans of the Asura Clan with absolute power!! 12 (+Alpha) Battle Stages! consists of combat stages with a variety of environmental combat styles. Rather than a bullet style that competes with the number of bullets, it borrows the shooting game elements such as aimed shooting that early shooting games shooting game elements such as aimed shooting that early shooters pursued. Martial Arts Factors , Flying swords Special skills!! Special skills, weapons, and characters from various civilizations appear. based on the original story, Use the martial arts system within the maintenance game. Instead of just playing a lot of ammunition Various weapons such as Spears, Axes, and memorization appear. It incorporates the mechanized martial arts style of the original “Battle Titan Mu-Hon”. and martial arts style of the original “Battle Titan Mu-Hon”. The Player 's journey begins when he receives an order from the Council of Elders. Robot Animation style ARTWORK. The game's art style is based on the giant robot anime style representative of the 90s, when the original game was made. The game's artistic atmosphere and mechanic design were organized to set it apart. A cartoonish intermission is added between each battle and intermission to run through the entire scenario. Level UP!, Equipment, Skill System With RPG elements, you can acquire / trade / five different pieces of equipment to adapt to different combat environments, including lasers, force cannons, force swords, force blades, extra combustion chambers, force shields, and more. . Detailed Description: It is 1650 in England. Five years have passed since Queen Charlotte I’s Royalists triumphed at the battle of Naseby. The parliamentary figureheads are dead, imprisoned, or scattered to the wind. Yet suspicion and paranoia still grip the nation. Hexfinder General Matthew Hopequins insists that hexcrafters and rebel exiles still plot the queen’s downfall. Others question the queen’s religious sympathies, and see Pontifex plotters around every corner. To the north, on the outskirts of Newcastle, a Royalist army sits in stalemate with Scottish forces. You will play a hexfinder in the employ of Queen Charlotte’s Anglican Church, tasked with seeking out the witches and warlocks (colloquially known as hexcrafters) who threaten her fair nation. It is June, and the summer solstice approaches. Charlotte announces her intention to return to Oxford, her seat of power during the most turbulent years of the civil war. Assigned to investigate the Oxfordshire villages along the queen’s route of travel, you will begin to uncover signs of heretical treachery at the heart of your sovereign’s court. Rumors abound that Oliver Cromwell cheated death at Naseby, sustained by diabolical and unholy sorceries… Be a zealous scourge of all heresy, a cynic who’s merely in it for the coin, or take a more charitable view of the accused. Pursue fame and prestige in Charlotte’s court through your deeds, and perhaps even catch her eye as a new favorite… Uncover treachery within the queen’s own court (this traitor will change in different playthroughs!) Or aid a parliamentary plot to bring down your monarch. Keep hexcrafting at arm’s length, or risk the suspicion of your peers by embracing the arcane and occult. Engage in thoroughly heretical smooching with four or five (depending on how ambitious I get this time!) different romantic partners. Name your horse, and (if sufficiently gifted/deluded) maybe even have a good chat with them. Wear a big black hat, like, all the time. A story-rich, text-based RPG, Hexfinder is a supernatural alt-historical adventure!

About the Game: King Smash - TopDown is a dynamic game with elements of a slasher. player destroys his opponents with a hammer, dodges bullets behind blocks, or breaks through blocks and opens up new opportunities for passing the level, thereby building tactics for each specific battle. Game Features: Level Destructibility, Beautiful Pixel-Art, Lots of Levels, Difficulty.

Detailed Description: You play as an inspector sent to the Tepas laboratory to investigate a series of strange events. Anomalies have been occurring in this lab for a long time, and your task is to find out what's going on. Prepare for a thrilling adventure that combines 2D pixel-art shooter elements with fast-paced action and hordes of enemies. In Lab Inspect, you'll experience dynamic gameplay, where you need to fight through crowds of enemies using a wide arsenal of weapons. You have a variety of firearms at your disposal, each effective in different situations. The enemies will keep you on your toes, attacking in waves and requiring quick reflexes and strategic thinking. Explore different levels of the laboratory, uncover its secrets, and fight bosses to gain access to new areas. The further you go, the more intense the gameplay becomes, with tougher and more numerous enemies. The sound design and game style create an atmosphere full of tension and danger. Game Features: A diverse selection of weapons to fight enemies. Hordes of opponents attacking in waves. Intense, hardcore gameplay that tests your skills. Vibrant pixel-art graphics with a unique aesthetic. An engaging storyline full of mysteries and unexpected twists.

Detailed Description: Heavily based on a famous Kart racing game, E3pdr is a PVP (Player vs Player), “Multiplayer”, “Multiplatform”, in which, controlling your puppet, you compete in several battles through different Eras in search of surprise boxes to find among thousands of “Easter Eggs” and items to acquire new skills, while fighting for survival.
